RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAKE SHORE DRIVE was away alertly to set a brisk pace up front down the backside, opened up through the turn under swift fractions, was asking for the wire at the furlong marker and held on by a diminishing margin at the finish. MIDNIGHT MOONSHINE tracked four wide down the backstretch, was throttled down to stalk the front three at the half, slipped up on the rail starting a rally in midturn, loomed the only threat at the top of the lane, was gaining steadily late but could not close the gap in time. ECHO WITH LAUGHTER was part of the tracking trio down the backstretch, settling on the inside just off the rail, chased the winner but to no avail while getting out through the turn and finished up mildly down the lane to hold on for third money crossing the finish line. UNEXPECTED OUTCOME (IRE) stalked near the rear down the back straight, made no headway around the bend and showed some late interest inside to close in for a minor role in the end. AMBER LIGHT broke outwards to begin, tracked the frontrunner between horses in the early going, was floated out chasing the winner on the turn and gave way in the four path in upper stretch. WILD CONVERSATION broke with the field but was void of early speed to trail down the backside, made little impact saving ground throughout the turn and could not get involved on the fence down the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARAMOS stalked widest in the four path into the first turn, improved three wide down the backstretch, was hard ridden commencing a run midway on the far turn, loomed four wide at the top of the lane, wore down rivals in mid-stretch and was going away crossing the finish line. TWIXTER tracked two wide outside on the first turn, took closer order down the back straight three wide on the outside, rallied for the lead in the three path at the quarter pole, briefly took command between foes at the furlong marker but was no match for the winner in deep stretch. ALL FOR HONOR tossed her head while veering in sharply on the break, trailed in the beginning, was allowed to find her feet down the backstretch, started to gain momentum picking up horses three wide at the half, continued to go around runners four wide through the turn, was in range in the five path in upper stretch, under left handed urging was laying in driving to the wire and surged at the line to capture the show money. SPANISH SERENADE tracked the frontrunner on the rail in the early stages, kept close tabs on the leader down the backside, bid between foes at the quarter pole, battled on the inside up front until the furlong marker and tired very late to just miss holding for third in the end. SUNYANI broke outwards on the break, regrouped to take this field into the first turn, set the pace unchallenged down the back straight, was collared outside by rivals at the quarter pole, offered little resistance turning for home and faded on the fence in mid-stretch. TAKE CHANCES stalked in the two path with runners on each side on the first turn, travelled in the third flight between foes at the half while under a ride to keep up, could not improve position in the final turn and was never a presence running to the finish line. ARNIE P stalked on the rail in the beginning, inched closer to the pacesetter inside at the half mile marker, was one paced saving ground on the final bend and showed little finish through the lane. WONT FORGET YOU stalked three wide between horses into the first turn, was shuffled back to settle near the rear down the back straight, could not offer a run through the far turn seeing the field and had little to give in the stretch drive.
